description:
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire and South Cumbria Foundation Trust (LCFT) has an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and skilled Band 7 clinician to lead our Community Adult Speech and Language Therapy Team. You will be highly motivated to lead a small, innovative team of therapists. You will be keen to liaise with a range of other professionals across the multi-disciplinary teams within the community and in-patient settings. You will also be a conscientious team player with excellent communication, interpersonal and analytical skills gained through previous acquired neurology experience and / or experience in the mental health clinical field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be independently managing a complex communication and swallowing caseload and will have completed your dysphagia competencies. You should have the ability to travel within Central Lancashire, Blackpool and the East of Lancashire and be able to manage and prioritise your own caseload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead our Community Adult Speech and Language Therapy team providing assessment and treatment for patients with a range of acquired communication and swallowing difficulties including Dementia and Neurological conditions. You will also be manage the SLT services at the Harbour, an acute in-patient mental health unit within Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust. You will support your team providing line management and clinical supervision and PDR and appraisal with staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to manage an established team and provide support, close liaison and collaboration with other professionals and carers. In return, we will provide you with regular professional and clinical supervision, support by senior therapists and professional lead SLT with the opportunity to network with other SLTs working within LSCFT. This is an innovative team and support is offered to a lead clinician with new ideas and who is keen to keep updated on new evidence-based practice skills and who wants to drive forward new service delivery options.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appointment is by interview and successful applicants will need to undergo the usual NHS pre-employment checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All candidates must be registered with RCSLT and HCPC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to an enhanced DBS check at the cost of £50.00, this will be deducted from your salary over the first 3 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information / to arrange a visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
